cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a framework for automated digital painting using reinforcement learning. The paper involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image synthesis and replication. The use of reinforcement learning (cs.AI) is the main focus of the paper, as it is used to train the painting agent. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses a variant of proximal policy optimization for training. The paper deals with graphics (cs.GR) as it involves painting on a digital canvas. Finally, the paper involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to create a system that can paint arbitrarily complex images in the desired style.
